         <h2>Behavior in the Airport</h2>
         <h2><small>by Bokshoi Sashimi</small></h2>
        <br>
        <br>
        <p>This just in...people at the airport behave in odd and mysterious ways. Imagine going to the airport, with a bunch of people traveling to and from. Most people will behave normally, but once in a while you'll come across someone whose
            behavior is shocking and creepy. What might surprise you is how common this occurs. Our investigator here at ABNN, Bokshoi Sashimi, waited for a flight from Phoenix to Flagstaff, Arizona to secretly observe people in the airport.
            The results of this study were not only shocking, but revolting. We here at ABNN expected odd behavior: running through the airport to get to the terminal, scratching your butts, picking your nose. But what Bokshoi Sashimi found
            at this particular stop was so mind-blowing that it made us at ABNN quite stunned: People tweezing their eyebrows at the Airport!</p>
        <div class='col-lg-6'>
            <blockquote>A woman is tweezing eyebrows in the airport
                <footer>Jenn's observation at the Phoenix Airport</footer>
            </blockquote>
        </div>
        <p>How did we find this out? Bokshoi was casually looking for any odd behaviors at the terminal when a passenger, Jenn Bodie, approached her with some shocking details. "Look over there, there's a woman tweezing her eyebrows at the airport"
            Jenn Bodie told the reporter. Bokshoi was shocked. How could this happen inside a busy airport terminal? While this may be extremely shocking, upon further analysis of airport behavior, we found this statistic to be startling:
            Many people who come to the airport are in a hurry and think they would be better off showing off their makeup procedures in public than waking up 15-30 minutes earlier to do it at home when it's most appropriate. Harvard University
            did a study on this and found that 60% of all airport passengers are either in a hurry or sleep-deprived. Shocking statistics to say the least.</p>
        <p>Bokshoi Sashimi did some further studying and made another fascinating discovery: People eat more unhealthy than usual at the airport. We don't know whether its because of a lack of choices or a lack of planning, but people are so
            unealthy eating that they would have french fries with ice cream. Even more shocking was that the passenger, Jenn Bodie, the same person who pointed out the Eyebrow Tweezer, was the person guilty of eating french fried and ice
            cream. We were amazed.</p>
        <p>Remember, be careful at the airport, you don't know what wacky behaviors you will come across at the airport, whether it's people who don't wash their hands in a very public place, or those who tweeze their eyebrows. Beware....</p>

